    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-07-08T07:35:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-07-08T07:35:00-05:00" n="341"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d341">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.154A/7–844: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ford</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-07-08T16:00:00+03:25"
                            >July 8, 1944—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received July 8—2:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>485. From Hoskins.<note n="77" xml:id="d341fn77">Harold B. Hoskins, Head of
                        Middle East Supply Center at Tehran.</note> Reference Legation’s 429, June
                        15.<note n="78" xml:id="d341fn78">Not printed; the Chargé had reported that
                        General Connolly had “raised question of release of American military
                        personnel serving with Iranian Road Transport Administration.”
                        (891.154A/6–1544)</note> Millspaugh, Black and Shields seriously disturbed
                    over impending withdrawal of American military personnel from Iranian Road
                    Transport Administration. Although General Connolly has acquiesced in token
                    releases for June and July, balance of men must be released by August 26 unless
                    orders are changed.</p>
                <p>How soon can we expect word from Landis as to results of his efforts with War
                    Department for continued service of these men in this vital work? They are
                    needed until January 1 if firm operating foundation is to be laid and at least
                    until November 15 when critical harvest collection period will be largely past.
                    Sent to Department as 485; repeated to Cairo for Short. [Hoskins.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Ford</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
